"{\"uid\": \"komonews.com-news-local-ruby-beach-olympic-national-park-kalaloch-forks-highway-101-visit-named-one-of-the-worlds-best-beaches-lonely-planet-new-book-western-washington-explore-travel-beaches-national-parks\", \"text\": \"Now  51\\u00b0  Tue  49\\u00b0  Wed  56\\u00b0  byKOMO News Staff  Ruby Beach in Olympic National Park has been recognized as one of the best beaches in the world!  The iconic beach was featured in a new book byLonely Planet, a well-known travel website that reviews destinations all over the world and shares insights for travelers. The bookBest Beaches: 100 of the World's Most Incredible Beacheshighlights beaches travelers should know about all around the globe.  Ruby Beach and Kalaloch are located on the southwest coast of the Olympic Peninsula and are accessible directly off Highway 101. Kalaloch is one of the most visited areas of Olympic National Park,according to the National Park Service(NPS).  The coastal waters off Ruby Beach are home to thousands of marine species, the NPS said.  Lonely Planet described Ruby Beach like a \\\"giant emptied his pockets on the shores... tree trunks are strewn like matchsticks. Sea stacks cluster like crumbled chocolates. And a colorful assortment of agates, garnets and sea glass add a touch of glitter to the captivating mess.\\\"  FILE - A photo of Ruby Beach in Washington state's Olympic National Park in January 2022. (Jimmy Bernhard / KOMO News)  Just about three and half hours away from downtown Seattle, Ruby Beach is certainly an option for a weekend getaway or early morning day trip. Been there before?Share your photos of Ruby Beach with us on Chime-In.  2025Sinclair, Inc.\"}"